</div><br>
<p> The amount of food consumed is influenced by the following factors: </p>
<p> Physiological structure (female or male (10-15% more) </p>
<p> Season (in the cold season they increase by 15%) </p>
<p> Exercise (15-30% more protein) </p>
<p> Pregnancy (1 half at 15-30%, the second at 40-100%) </p>
<p> Flowing and sham (reduced by 20-40%) </p>
<p> Tribal use of a dog from 2 times per month (more by 10-30%) </p>
<p> Age (an older dog reduces carbohydrates by 15-20%) </p>
<p style = "font-weight: bold;"> You can give: </p>
<p> MEAT muscular (raw (frozen for 3 days) or boiled) - 25-30% of the daily diet - daily: </p>
<p> - steam beef (not veal, because it has less nutrients); </p>
<p> - not fat, young lamb; </p>
<p> - beef scar (stomach), raw, peeled or not cleaned, well washed, scalded with boiling water - (very carefully, give up to 7 months, there may be a disorder); </p>
<p> - not fat beef, lamb groin (raw, boiled). </p>
<p> Pashina is the place in the carcass where the internal organs are located; </p>
<p> - raw beef leg (cut from the leg), as if to brawn - from 3 months. Give gnawing leg to strengthen and clean the teeth; </p>
<p> - tails, cartilaginous bones (raw only); </p>
<p> - offal (heart - raw, liver and spleen - cook, (udder and lungs are not often given, do not give kidneys). </p>
<p> Broths can be, but they are poorly digested. </p>
<p> FISH is sea, boiled (diet doubles, as it is poorer in protein) - 1 time per week: </p>
<p> - fillet of hake, cod, pollock (contain non-absorbable iron) </p>
<p> River can not be given. </p>
<p> Red fish is a high allergen. </p>
<p> BIRD (raw, boiled) - 1-2 times a week: </p>
<p> - chicken </p>
<p> - Turkey (minced turkey - ideal puppy food) </p>
<p> Chicken offal (stomachs, liver) is only rarely given and only boiled. </p>
<p> You can not tubular and ANY boiled bones, chicken legs, etc. May injure the esophagus. </p>
<p> Cooked cereals - daily: </p>
<p> - rice (must be salted, so rice removes salt from the body, mineral metabolism is disturbed); </p>
<p> - buckwheat; </p>
<p> - semolina (for recovering dogs only); </p>
<p> - a mixture of 0.5 rice + 0.5 buckwheat. </p>
<p> You can not - oatmeal, barley, peas, pasta, fresh bread. </p>
<p> Croutons made from white bran or stale bread are given as a delicacy. </p>
<p> FAMILY PRODUCTS - daily: </p>
<p> - kefir, biokefir, ryazhenka, sour cream, yogurt 1%; </p>
<p> - curd (calcined) no more than 5%. </p>
<p> Cheese (10%) is given as a treat, occasionally, as it is too salty for dogs. </p>
<p> Milk is given only to puppies up to 3 months. </p>
<p> EGGS (boiled, raw) - once a week </p>
<p> - Chicken - 1-2 pieces, - better quail - 3-6 pieces. </p>
<p> FRUITS and BERRIES - on request in moderate quantities: </p>
<p> - green apples with sour. You can give a little daily. Adult dogs do not always eat. </p>
<p> Red apples can cause an allergic reaction. </p>
<p> - plums, apricots, kiwi, bananas (a little); </p>
<p> - any berries; </p>
<p> - watermelon, melon. </p>
<p> Fruits should be grown in a season without nitrates. </p>
<p> Dried fruits give occasionally as a treat. </p>
<p> - prunes; </p>
<p> - dried apricots. </p>
<p> They contain a lot of beneficial trace elements. </p>
<p> Raisins, grapes, avocados are not allowed. </p>
<p> You can give 1 teaspoon of honey once a week (if there are no allergic reactions). </p>
<p> VEGETABLES - 20% of the daily diet - daily: </p>
<p> - broccoli, cauliflower; </p>
<p> - zucchini or pumpkin, cucumbers in any form; </p>
<p> - carrots, raw, grated on a fine grater. You can give each day for 1 tablespoon (or more) with food or 1-2 times a week (always with butter). </p>
<p> Vegetables mainly have a laxative effect on the digestive tract. </p>
<p> GREEN - 2-3 times a week: </p>
<p> - dill, parsley; </p>
<p> - Salad - Chinese cabbage. Chop smaller, slightly choke or boil (do not fry), add to food. It is possible in the form of mashed potatoes. </p>
<p> You can not - onions. </p>
<p> You can germinate oats (give green shoots). </p>
<p> VEGETABLE OIL for the first cold-pressed daily: </p>
<p> - olive, corn, sunflower, flaxseed. Add to food 1 tbsp. spoon. </p>
<p> Fish oil without vitamins 0.5 to 1 teaspoon - in food. With natural feeding, vitamins are mandatory! </p>
